steps to remove classnotfoundexception while using junit in eclipse even when your .class is available.

-->
so it is a problem with the classpath that you need to set in run configuration of junit.

--> 
in classpath tab ---> User Entries --> click on advannced tab---> add folders -->then select the classes folder in the module where your testclass available.

--> apply and run ...do same if getting error for another class file.


Note: Follow same process while using PIT, if you are getting zero or full mutation coverage without any report.

